author: Phil Hunt
title: Waukon wins against New Hampton, 46-13
text:
Waukon wins against New Hampton, 46-13 - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: Waukon wins against New Hampton, 46-13 Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> 
Good matchup tonight in 2A district 3. 8th ranked Waukon with a 5-1 record visits 4-2 New Hampton. 
But the Chickasaws lead district Waukon gets off to a fast start. 
Peyton hesse from shotgun...he fires to Wyatt Wille. Wille fights his way to the five for a fifteen yard gain. 
Two plays later...Hesse connects with Haden Hammel for the five yard TD and a six nothing lead. 
Waukon's defense came to play as well. The chickasaws passing, the ball is tipped then picked by Wyatt Wille. He races down the sideline and is knocked out at the eight. 
Two plays later...Hesse finds Tanner Mathis wide open for the easy 5 yard t-d. A two point conversion would make it fourteen nothing Waukon. 
The chickasaw's would not go quietly. Waukon threatening at the New Hampton five. Hesse passing but he over throws his target. Adam Wurzer makes a nice grab for the interception. 
But it's waukon rolling to a big victory tonight with a 46-13 win. Can't Find Something? 500 Fourth St. Waterloo, IA 50703 News: (319) 291-1200
